sentences: Daniel Menche (born December 4, 1969) is an American experimental musician and multidisciplinary artist from  Portland, Oregon.

Since 1989 he has recorded many albums that are categorized as electro-acoustic, noise music, dark ambient music, abstract, avant-garde, experimental, field recordings, drone, minimalist music, percussion and soundtrack film music.
Daniel Menche has performed hundreds of concerts since 1991.
Multimedia art and music festivals specializing in experimental music and video art have showcased Menche’s work since 1995.
Since 2008 Daniel Menche has created abstract video art with mostly his own music as the soundtrack.
Menche’s videos were presented at the 2012 MUTEK festival at Montreal, Canada.

Since 2007 Daniel Menche has been employed as a school librarian and is a literacy advocate for children.
